The paper deals with the problem of estimating a discrete distribution under privacy constraints, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also proposes a new family of schemes that improve the performance of existing schemes, which involves analyzing the expected estimation loss under different metrics, a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and statistics (cs.SI).
